    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_86738701" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/86738701" />
    <a title="Tony" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33771-tony"><img alt="Tony" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1292869016p2/33771.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/86738701?book_show_action=true">Jan 25, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tony" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tony" href="/user/show/33771-tony">Tony</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780394400266" href="/book/show/369050.A_Distant_Mirror">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33771-tony?shelf=top-10-2010">top-10-2010</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer86738701" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14413498721044085838">The Calamitous 14th Century: a time of war, class struggle, taxation, endless litigation, ravaging disease, religious intolerance, Christian versus Moslem, feckless leaders, plenty of lust, torture, self-interest -- &apos;a distant mirror&apos; indeed. We are not so different. Look back or just look around.<br/><br/>And that is the point, I think, of this wonderful work of history and <u>literature</u>. Tuchman&apos;s wit and erudition are on full display.<br/><br/>Sometimes the reading went very slow, but only because it all seemed so </span>
  <span id="freeText14413498721044085838" style="display:none">The Calamitous 14th Century: a time of war, class struggle, taxation, endless litigation, ravaging disease, religious intolerance, Christian versus Moslem, feckless leaders, plenty of lust, torture, self-interest -- 'a distant mirror' indeed. We are not so different. Look back or just look around.<br /><br />And that is the point, I think, of this wonderful work of history and <u>literature</u>. Tuchman's wit and erudition are on full display.<br /><br />Sometimes the reading went very slow, but only because it all seemed so important. This is History of the highest rank.</span>
